    body: 'What is Time Travel in Snowflake and how does it differ from Fail-Safe?',
    answer: 'Time Travel allows you to query, clone, or restore data to any point within a configurable retention period (1-90 days for Enterprise). Use AT or BEFORE clause: SELECT * FROM orders AT(TIMESTAMP => \'2026-01-15 10:00:00\'). Fail-Safe is Snowflake-managed, non-self-service disaster recovery — 7 additional days after Time Travel expires. You cannot query Fail-Safe data yourself; only Snowflake support can restore it. Time Travel costs storage (all historical micro-partitions are retained). Best practice: set TIME_TRAVEL_IN_DAYS=7 for most tables, 90 only for critical tables to control cost.',
