    body: 'What are Airflow Sensors and when would you use a FileSensor vs an HttpSensor vs an ExternalTaskSensor?',
    answer: 'Sensors are operators that poke an external condition repeatedly (poke_mode) or defer execution (reschedule mode, Airflow 2.2+). FileSensor: waits for a file to appear on a filesystem or S3 — use when upstream drops a data file before your ETL should run. HttpSensor: polls an HTTP endpoint until it returns success — use for API-driven upstream readiness checks. ExternalTaskSensor: waits for a task/DAG in a different DAG to complete — use for cross-DAG dependencies. Best practice: always set poke_interval and timeout; use mode="reschedule" to free up the worker slot while waiting instead of blocking it indefinitely.',
