    answer: 'Single-server in-memory counters do not work across 100 servers — each has a different count. Solution: centralized Redis with sliding window algorithm. Redis INCR + EXPIRE: key = user_id:minute_bucket. INCR atomically increments, EXPIRE sets 60s TTL. If count > 1000, return 429. Problem: minute boundary bursts. Fix: sliding window log (store request timestamps in Redis sorted set, count within last 60s) or token bucket in Redis using Lua scripts for atomicity. For global scale: Redis Cluster with consistent hashing. Fallback: if Redis is down, fail open (allow traffic) with local rate limiting as a backstop.',
