    tech: [],
    experience: '4-8 years',
    answer: 'WiredTiger (default since MongoDB 3.2): MVCC-based document-level concurrency. Multiple readers never block each other. Writers only lock the specific document. MMAPv1: collection-level locking (one write blocked all writes to the collection). WiredTiger also has better compression (snappy/zlib), journal compression, and cache management (50% of RAM by default). Much better for mixed read-write workloads.',
