    verifyCount: 4, upvotes: 13, daysAgo: 49, asked: 51,
    tech: [],
    experience: '5-9 years',
    answer: 'Dual-write problem: writing to DB and publishing to Kafka in the same operation — if DB succeeds but Kafka fails (or vice versa), systems are inconsistent. Outbox: write event to an outbox table in the SAME DB transaction as the business data. A separate process (Debezium CDC or polling) reads outbox table and publishes to Kafka. Atomicity of DB transaction guarantees both business data and event are written together.',
