    tech: [],
    experience: '3-6 years',
    answer: 'Pessimistic locking: lock the row before reading (SELECT FOR UPDATE). No other transaction can modify it. Use when conflicts are frequent. Optimistic locking: read row + version number. Update only if version unchanged (UPDATE SET version=v+1 WHERE id=X AND version=v). Retry on failure. Use when conflicts are rare (most reads/writes don\'t conflict). ORM support: JPA @Version annotation. Optimistic is better for high-read low-write scenarios.',
