    experience: '3-6 years',
    answer: 'Deadlock: Thread A holds Lock 1, waits for Lock 2. Thread B holds Lock 2, waits for Lock 1. Both wait forever. Prevention: 1) Lock ordering: always acquire locks in the same order (A and B both: lock1 first, then lock2). 2) Lock timeout: tryLock(timeout) returns false if can\'t acquire — break out and retry. 3) Avoid nested locking where possible. 4) Use higher-level concurrency (java.util.concurrent, ConcurrentHashMap). 5) Detect with thread dumps (jstack shows BLOCKED threads). 6) Use deadlock detection algorithms in monitoring.',
