    tech: [],
    experience: '4-7 years',
    answer: 'V8 uses generational GC. Young generation (Scavenger): most objects die young. Minor GC: fast, frequent, collects young gen. Major GC (Mark-Sweep-Compact): full heap scan, marks reachable objects, sweeps unreachable, compacts to reduce fragmentation. GC pauses: major GC is stop-the-world (everything pauses). V8 uses incremental marking, concurrent marking, and parallel compaction to reduce pause times. Causes: creating many short-lived objects, long-lived caches, closures holding large data.',
